Pakistan May Increase Government Salaries by 15%, Recorder Says

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-05-18T04:59:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/pakistan-may-increase-government-salaries-by-15-recorder-says.html
Pakistan  may raise the salaries of
government employees by 15 percent in the federal budget for the
year starting July 1, the Business Recorder newspaper  reported ,
without saying where it got the information. This may cost the
exchequer 13.5 billion rupees ($158 million), the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khurrum Anis in Karachi at 
 kkhan14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor on this story:
